  "title": "Marketing Manager / Marketing Associate (Gaming)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Summary</strong><br />We are looking for a marketing professional with a strong understanding of <strong>game growth and community building</strong>. This role focuses on growing and managing our game community across <strong>Steam, Discord, and social channels</strong>, working closely with the game and product team to drive engagement, retention, and long-term community health.</p><p>(Level and scope will be adjusted based on experience.)</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Plan and execute <strong>community growth strategies</strong> for a game title</p></li><li><p>Manage and grow communities on <strong>Steam, Discord, and social platforms</strong></p></li><li><p>Create and manage <strong>Steam announcements, patch notes, and update communications</strong></p></li><li><p>Monitor player feedback, sentiment, and engagement, and work with the team to improve community experience</p></li><li><p>Support game launches, updates, live events, and community initiatives</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with developers/designers to align game updates with community messaging</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Experience or strong familiarity with <strong>gaming communities</strong> (PC, console, or mobile)</p></li><li><p>Understanding of how <strong>player engagement and retention</strong> work in games</p></li><li><p>Experience managing or contributing to <strong>online communities</strong> (Discord, forums, social platforms)</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and coordination skills</p></li><li><p>Passion for games and player communities</p></li></ul><h3>Nice to Have</h3><ul><li><p>Experience with Steam community management</p></li><li><p>Background in game design, live-ops, or game publishing</p></li><li><p>Experience supporting game launches or live-service games</p></li></ul>",
